# Expansion Polymorphism
# Uses: Expansion (!), Structural Duck Typing

# Define two different shapes with an 'x' field
# Point x y
# Player id x health

# Generic function that doesn't care about the type
# as long as it has field 'x'
: get_x !obj
    get !obj x 0

# Test calls (handled by compiler monomorphization)
# @ get_x new Point 1
# @ get_x new Player 1
